key:
starfarer_obf.jar:com/fs/starfarer/campaign/command/IntelIncomePanel.class#"Your expenses have exceeded both your income and your available credits.

If this continues for more than a month, some cr~"@3cc936c5
original:
Your expenses have exceeded both your income and your available credits.

If this continues for more than a month, some crew may leave next time you're in port, and other undertakings requiring credit expenditures may fail.

Shutting down industries on colonies you control is a quick way to both reduce your expenses and get back most of the credits used to establish them.
translation:
你的月收入和星币余额已经无法覆盖你的支出。

如果这种情况持续超过一个月，下次你靠港时，部分船员可能会选择离开，且其他需要花费星币的项目也可能会失败。

关停你控制的殖民地上的工业设施是迅速减少支出并回收大部分投资工业设施的星币的有效方法。

Save game operation produced a corrupted file. Your previous save is unaffected.

Please try saving again; if that doesn't work, use the "Save Copy" option from the campaign menu.

key: starfarer_obf.jar:com/fs/starfarer/campaign/ui/marketinfo/CommodityDetailDialog.class#"A market chooses a single source to get its supply of a commodity. Should that source go away or become less desirable, th~"@eec09bdb
original:
A market chooses a single source to get its supply of a commodity. Should that source go away or become less desirable, the next best source will be used. In order of importance, a market will prefer a supplier that:

- can satisfy more of the demand
- is local to the market
- has higher accessibility from the market
translation:
A market chooses a single source to get its supply of a commodity. Should that source go away or become less desirable, the next best source will be used. In order of importance, a market will prefer a supplier that:

- can satisfy more of the demand

starfarer_obf.jar:com/fs/starfarer/campaign/ui/marketinfo/cdd/CommodityDetailDialogV2$1.class#"Only show colonies that are either suffering from a shortage or have excess stockpiles.

Colonies with excess stockpiles h~"@c199b425
original:
Only show colonies that are either suffering from a shortage or have excess stockpiles.

Colonies with excess stockpiles have more of the goods available on the open market and have lower prices.

Colonies with shortages have less or none available for sale, and have higher prices.
translation:
只显示那些正在经历库存短缺或拥有过剩库存的殖民地。

拥有过剩库存的殖民地在其 公开市场 上有更多商品供应，价格也较低。

出现短缺的殖民地可供出售的商品数量较少，甚至完全没有库存可用，价格也相对较高。

original:
Maximum number of units capable of being exported by a single producer. Imports can increase the number of units available up to this number. 

For example, if a colony needs 5 units of a commodity, but the maximum export is 4, then that colony will only have 4 units, and a "global shortage" of 1.
translation:
单个供应源能够出口的最大商品数量。进口量的最大值也等同于此值。

例如，如果某个殖民地需要 5 单位的某种商品，但最大出口量只有 4 单位，那么该殖民地就只能获得 4 单位，并 "短缺" 1个单位。

Are you sure?

Ordering a full assault will cancel all existing assignments and make your ships engage the enemy forces more aggressively, potentially exposing them to greater danger.

你确定吗？

下令 全面进攻 将取消所有指令，并使你的舰队非常积极地进攻，这可能让它们暴露于更大的威胁之下。

original:
Excellent, your forces are in position! Now, let's order a strike on the unsuspecting enemy cruiser. <highlight>Click on it and select "Strike" from the context menu.</highlight>

After that's done, you can either watch the bombers carry out their strike ("Show Video Feed" from their context menu) or get into the battle yourself.

Either way, make sure the enemy cruiser is destroyed.
translation:
干得漂亮，您的舰队已各就各位！现在，让我们打击那艘毫无防备的敌方巡洋舰。<highlight>点击它并在命令列表中选择 "战机攻击"。</highlight>
在指派命令之后，您可以欣赏轰炸机的攻击过程 (可以在命令列表中选择 "接通视频信号") 或亲自加入战斗。

无论如何，将敌方巡洋舰彻底摧毁。

original:
Refitting a ship will temporarily decrease its CR based on the number of ordnance points changed. The new CR value - should the refit be carried out - is indicated by the dimmed portion of the CR bar. 

Using unspent ordnance points will not bring CR down into malfunction range, and refitting at a port will not reduce CR at all.
translation:
Refitting a ship will temporarily decrease its CR based on the number of ordnance points changed. The new CR value - should the refit be carried out - is indicated by the dimmed portion of the CR bar.
